      E for Extortion
   =20
 =20
Leon Black, the former head of Apollo Global Management Inc., allegedly had=
 an extramarital affair with a woman 30 years younger than him, paid her mi=
llions of dollars during their sexual relationship, secretly recorded their=
 conversations, and=C2=A0spent millions more dollars to conceal the affair =
from the directors and clients of his firm. When I say =E2=80=9Callegedly=
=E2=80=9D I mean that=E2=80=99s what=C2=A0he=C2=A0alleges;  that=E2=80=99s =
his=C2=A0defense=C2=A0of his actions.=C2=A0Her=C2=A0allegations are much wo=
rse; she claims that he abused and assaulted her and then threatened her to=
 keep her silent. He claims that she is lying and that she has been extorti=
ng money out of him for years.In any case they seem to agree that, after th=
eir affair ended, they had lunch at the Four Seasons in 2015 and signed a c=
ontract providing that Black would pay her $100,000 a month for 15 years. H=
ere is an amazing detail from Black=E2=80=99s court filing:After the partie=
s entered into the Agreement, Mr. Black set up a new account from which to =
make the monthly payments to Ganieva, which he called =E2=80=9CE Trust.=E2=
=80=9D In her Complaint, Ganieva states that she =E2=80=9Chas no knowledge =
as to why payments began from the =E2=80=98E Trust=E2=80=99 or what it is.=
=E2=80=9D (Cplt. =C2=B6 73). To be very clear: the =E2=80=9CE=E2=80=9D in =
=E2=80=9CE Trust=E2=80=9D stands for =E2=80=9CExtortion.=E2=80=9DI =E2=80=
=A6=C2=A0wow, okay. We talk from  time to  time around here about the euphe=
misms that you should or should not use when you are paying or accepting br=
ibes. We have even=C2=A0talked=C2=A0about the  euphemisms that you should u=
se when you are demanding blackmail. (=E2=80=9CLegal settlement,=E2=80=9D v=
ery good.) On the other hand, if you are=C2=A0paying blackmail, and if your=
 lawyers are drafting the blackmail contract and setting up the blackmail l=
egal entities, I think it is probably a good idea to avoid euphemism as far=
 as possible? Sign a Blackmail Agreement, pay the money through the I Am Be=
ing Extorted Trust, keep=C2=A0all the documentation as explicit as possible=
. That way, if you ever change your mind about paying, or=C2=A0if your blac=
kmailer changes her mind and demands more money,=C2=A0you=C2=A0can blackmai=
l=C2=A0her: =E2=80=9CHey, I=E2=80=99ve been paying you all this clearly lab=
eled blackmail for years now, you wouldn=E2=80=99t want the police to find =
out about that would you?=E2=80=9D I am not sure, though, that calling it t=
he =E2=80=9CE Trust,=E2=80=9D and not telling her what it stands for, accom=
plishes that goal.
